        Applies the given function to the values contained in the given results. If any of the results is not a success, then the function is not called at all, and a failure is returned. The returned failure is either the failure contained in the first, or in the second result.

      • apply

        public static <T,U,R> io.vavr.control.Try<R> apply(BiFunction<T,U,io.vavr.control.Try<R>> f,
                                                   Supplier<io.vavr.control.Try<T>> x,
                                                   Supplier<io.vavr.control.Try<U>> y)
        Applies the given function to the values returned by the given suppliers. If any of the results is not a success, then the function is not called at all, and a failure is returned. If the first result is not a success, then the second supplier will not be called. The returned failure is either the failure contained in the first, or in the second result.
